After pip install, the package would not run, saying it can not import
ui.
This was, because the sub-packages of arxiv_filter were not added to the
setup.py.

Fixed by now using find_packages() of setuptools

Fixes parsing when copy-paste from thunderbird

Fixes #2

When doing a copy-paste of the E-Mail text from thunderbird under linux,
the line endings are \r\n instead of \n.
When drag-n-dropping from the same thunderbird client, the line endings
are \n.

This bug fix unifies the line-ending, before parsing. Therefore removing
any issue that might have also occured on a windows computer.

Fixes #12

Fixes wrong value for setStretch

- setStrech factor should be an int
- In Qt6, there is actual type checking in python, and setting the value
  0.01 (float) leads to an exception.
- Setting 0 instead of 0.01 one would expect the same behaviour as
  before, as the 0.01 internally of QT would have anyway been casted to
  int (and thus to 0).
